WEBVTT

00:07.780 --> 00:10.800
Hi there! Welcome to
this video, where we

00:10.800 --> 00:12.340
are going to learn
about what it means

00:12.340 --> 00:14.840
to be resilient in
digital environments.

00:14.940 --> 00:17.420
The goal of the
presentation is to

00:17.420 --> 00:18.860
help you to
understand what

00:18.860 --> 00:21.180
resilience is, and
things that you can

00:21.180 --> 00:23.040
do to help yourself
to become more

00:23.040 --> 00:26.680
resilient in digital
environments. In the

00:26.680 --> 00:29.440
video, firstly, we
will look at what we

00:29.440 --> 00:32.220
mean by resilience.
Then, we will look at

00:32.220 --> 00:34.100
things we can do to
help us to become

00:34.100 --> 00:38.080
more resilient.
According to the

00:38.080 --> 00:39.920
dictionary,
resilience is the

00:39.920 --> 00:42.460
ability to cope when
exposed to challenges

00:42.460 --> 00:45.140
or things that cause
you to feel stressed.

00:45.780 --> 00:47.860
Resilience allows
people to bounce back

00:47.860 --> 00:51.880
by adapting to stress
in healthy ways. The

00:51.880 --> 00:53.760
digital world can
sometimes expose us

00:53.760 --> 00:55.420
to a number of
challenges such as

00:55.420 --> 00:58.100
negative or hateful
comments, identity

00:58.100 --> 01:00.640
theft and fraud, and
exclusion by others

01:00.640 --> 01:03.820
on social media. This
can leave us feeling

01:03.820 --> 01:06.980
sad, anxious, angry,
or a lot of different

01:06.980 --> 01:10.260
emotions. We may also
feel a bit powerless

01:10.260 --> 01:13.720
and not know what to
do. Sometimes we may

01:13.720 --> 01:15.760
be able to handle the
challenges we face by

01:15.760 --> 01:18.940
being resilient.
Resilience is a skill

01:18.940 --> 01:20.820
, and we can learn
how to be resilient

01:20.820 --> 01:22.900
and bounce forward
from these challenges

01:22.900 --> 01:24.900
, get up, learn from
what you have

01:24.900 --> 01:26.900
experienced, and move
forwards.

01:30.580 --> 01:34.200
Step 1. Acknowledging
the challenge and, or

01:34.200 --> 01:36.820
, stressor, and using
problem-solving

01:36.820 --> 01:39.780
technique to resolve
the issue. It shows

01:39.780 --> 01:41.540
wisdom to acknowledge
that there is a

01:41.540 --> 01:43.820
challenge. This is a
good starting point

01:43.820 --> 01:46.940
to solving the
challenge. Step 2.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.760
Seeking support to
gain an alternative

01:48.760 --> 01:51.220
viewpoint on the
issue. You can

01:51.220 --> 01:52.900
sometimes solve
challenges on your

01:52.900 --> 01:55.440
own. Other times it
can be wise to accept

01:55.440 --> 01:57.860
that you need help
and to ask for help.

01:58.040 --> 02:00.000
We can chat to
someone we trust,

02:00.000 --> 02:02.520
like a parent or a
teacher, for help, or

02:02.520 --> 02:06.260
call kids' helpline
for a chat. Step 3.

02:06.560 --> 02:08.600
Implementing self
-care strategies.

02:09.320 --> 02:11.380
Sometimes you can
find small things

02:11.380 --> 02:13.140
that help you to calm
your thoughts and

02:13.140 --> 02:15.660
feelings. This can
help you think more

02:15.660 --> 02:18.800
clearly and be more
resilient. These are

02:18.800 --> 02:21.480
called coping
strategies, or self

02:21.480 --> 02:24.360
-care strategies. It
is wise to know what

02:24.360 --> 02:26.840
helps you. What
little things help

02:26.840 --> 02:30.060
you feel calmer? Some
examples of things

02:30.060 --> 02:32.080
that people do to
help them to cope and

02:32.080 --> 02:33.780
care for themselves
when facing

02:33.780 --> 02:36.780
challenges are Draw,
play sport, slow

02:36.780 --> 02:39.360
breathing, spend time
with a pet, listen to

02:39.360 --> 02:42.600
music, sing, dance,
read a book, write in

02:42.600 --> 02:45.220
a journal, help
someone else, gaming,

02:45.220 --> 02:48.980
shower, sleep. Step 4
. Gain sufficient

02:48.980 --> 02:51.100
distance from the
problem to alleviate

02:51.100 --> 02:54.160
some of the pressure.
Sometimes it can be

02:54.160 --> 02:56.460
wise to take a break
and do something that

02:56.460 --> 02:59.400
you enjoy. This can
help you to get some

02:59.400 --> 03:00.980
distance from the
challenge you are

03:00.980 --> 03:03.920
facing. It can give
you a new perspective

03:03.920 --> 03:08.240
and help you to feel
better. Step 5.

03:08.540 --> 03:10.160
Recognizing that
everyone makes

03:10.160 --> 03:13.480
mistakes. It can also
help to reflect over

03:13.480 --> 03:16.320
the challenging
situation. Is there

03:16.320 --> 03:18.060
something that you
can learn from the

03:18.060 --> 03:20.860
situation? Is there
something positive

03:20.860 --> 03:22.640
that you can take
from the experience

03:22.640 --> 03:24.720
that may help you or
someone else in the

03:24.720 --> 03:29.100
future? Thank you for
watching. Do not

03:29.100 --> 03:31.540
forget to watch other
videos in our series.

03:31.540 --> 03:33.040
Do not forget to
watch other videos in

03:33.040 --> 03:33.160
the right videos.
There are very many

03:33.160 --> 03:34.140
videos in theADAY.
Those are not good

